ialects« documents contact between the German and Yiddish languages, with special reference to German dialects. The material was taken from German dialect dictionaries, compiled systematically and revised lexicographically and etymologically. The introductory chapters of the dictionary deal with aspects of historical and linguistic integration, the state of research on the subject, the sources drawn upon, and Hebrew and Aramaic etymologies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexDialectsvDictionaries. 0aGerman languagexForeign words and phrasesxYiddishvDictionaries. 4aDeutsch. 4aJiddisch. 4aLehnwort. 4aMundart. 4aWörterbuch. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS0 cprintz978348439102440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091505140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110915051423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110915051/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014